ww.businessinsider.com%2Fjack-dorsey-block-memo-new-era-white-collar-layoffs-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etech%20bloodbath%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20job%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFriday's%20shockingly%20weak%20jobs%20report%20showed%20a%20loss%20of%2092%2C000%20jobs%20in%20February%20across%20the%20broader%20economy%2C%20far%20below%20the%20expected%20gain%20of%2055%2C000%20jobs.%20After%20the%20release%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-report-february-data-live-updates-2026-3%23the-economy-is-in-a-techpocalypse%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520economy%2520is%2520in%2520a%2520techpocalypse%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeconomist%20Joseph%20Politano%3C%2Fa%3E%20posted%20on%20X%20that%20the%20tech%20sector%20has%20had%20an%20especially%20rough%20couple%20of%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20a%20while%2C%20you%20could%20at%20least%20say%20we're%20not%20gaining%20jobs%20the%20way%20we%20used%20to%2C%20but%20we're%20not%20losing%20them.%20Everything's%20kind%20of%20stagnant%2C%26quot%3B%20Politano%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThat%20has%2C%20over%20the%20last%20year%2C%20completely%20changed%2C%20where%20it's%20losing%20jobs%20again%20at%20one%20of%20the%20most%20rapid%20rates%20of%20the%20last%2020%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20job%20losses%20now%20outpace%20past%20downturns%20in%202008%20and%202020%2C%20per%20Politano.%20Historically%2C%20Politano%20said%2C%20the%20US%20would%20usually%20be%20adding%20around%20100%2C000%20to%20300%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhottest-job-in-tech-writing-words-ai-hiring-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejobs%20in%20tech%3C%2Fa%3E%20annually%3B%20even%20when%20there%20have%20been%20some%20pullbacks%2C%20there's%20generally%20a%20quick%20rebound.%20But%20not%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FzmuHl%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Line%20chart%20of%20the%20year-over-year%20change%20in%20tech%20employment%20since%201991%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FzmuHl%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAlready%2C%20Politano%20said%2C%20this%20moment%20is%20clearly%20and%20significantly%20worse%20for%20the%20sector%20than%20the%202020%20recession%2C%20and%20slightly%20worse%20than%202008.%20He%20thinks%20the%20most%20apt%20comparison%20is%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbi-today-dot-com-bubble-bursting-anniversary-history-repeating-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edot-com%20bust%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20although%20today's%20situation%20still%20isn't%20quite%20as%20dire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20the%20only%20thing%20that%20you%20can%20compare%20it%20to%20is%20the%20worst%20tech%20job%20recession%20of%20all%20time%20is%20pretty%20bad%2C%26quot%3B%20Politano%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20length%20is%20really%20important%20here.%20It's%20been%20three%20years%20of%20job%20losses.%20It%20took%20only%20about%20four%20years%20for%20recovery%20to%20start%20from%20the%20dot-com%20bust%2C%20for%20tech%20to%20start%20rehiring%20at%20a%20semi-normal%20rate%20again.%20The%20fact%20that%20we're%20now%20three%20years%20into%20this%20and%20it's%20actually%20getting%20worse%20is%20a%20really%20big%20deal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAre%20you%20impacted%20by%20the%20current%20tech%20job%20market%3F%20Contact%20these%20reporters%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajkaplan%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejkaplan%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amhoff%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emhoff%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20as%20Cory%20Stahle%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20Indeed%20Hiring%20Lab%2C%20notes%2C%20it's%20not%20just%20tech%20that's%20down%20in%20the%20dumps.%20Manufacturing%2C%20which%20has%20been%20cooling%20for%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20saw%20employment%20fall%2C%20as%20did%20the%20government%20sector.%20Healthcare%2C%20which%20had%20been%20propping%20up%20the%20job%20market%2C%20lost%20jobs%20in%20February%2C%20exacerbated%20by%20a%20roughly%20monthlong%20Kaiser%20Permanente%20strike.%20%26quot%3BEverything%20was%20looking%20pretty%20weak%20by%20different%20industries%2C%26quot%3B%20Stahle%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZipRecruiter%20economist%20Nicole%20Bachaud%20said%20February's%20losses%20in%20tech-related%20sectors%20were%20similar%20to%20recent%20trends.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20look%20at%20information%20continue%20to%20see%20a%20decline%2C%20and%20then%20the%20professional%20and%20business%20services%2C%20a%20little%20bit%20soft%2C%20but%20I%20wouldn't%20say%20that%20was%20necessarily%20an%20out-of-place%20movement%20for%20that%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20Bachaud%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20been%20a%20lot%20of%20headlines%20looking%20at%20layoffs%20in%20tech%20or%20big%20changes%20at%20certain%20employers%20in%20tech%2C%20but%20overall%2C%20the%20layoff%20rate%20has%20been%20very%20low%20and%20stable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhighest-unemployment-rates-college-majors-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecollege%20grads%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20leaned%20into%20STEM%20and%20other%20people%20seeking%20their%20first%20jobs%20could%20be%20especially%20hard%20hit%20by%20the%20tech%20hiring%20downturn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20seen%20a%20lot%20about%20recent%20graduates%20struggling%20to%20find%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20Stahle%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20really%20feel%20for%20those%20people%20who%20started%20studying%20computer%20science%20four%20or%20five%20years%20ago%20and%20were%20told%20that%2C%20'Hey%2C%20this%20is%20a%20surefire%20way%20to%20get%20in%20the%20labor%20market%2C%20make%20a%20good%20salary%2C'%20and%20now%20we're%20seeing%20just%20a%20continuation%20of%20this%20trend%20of%20fewer%20and%20fewer%20hires%20being%20made%20in%20the%20tech%20sector%2C%26quot%3B%20Stahle%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20job%20numbers%20also%20don't%20yet%20reflect%20the%20sweeping%20layoffs%20from%20Block%2C%20which%20excised%20nearly%20half%20its%20workforce%20last%20week.%20In%20his%20announcement%20outlining%20the%20cuts%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblock-lay-off-4000-employees-read-jack-dorseys-memo-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECEO%20Jack%20Dorsey%3C%2Fa%3E%20cited%20AI%20as%20a%20reason%2C%20saying%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20intelligence%20tools%20we're%20creating%20and%20using%2C%20paired%20with%20smaller%20and%20flatter%20teams%2C%20are%20enabling%20a%20new%20way%20of%20working.%26quot%3B%20Some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblock-layoffs-jack-dorsey-gratitude-meeting-employee-reaction-ai-integration-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaid-off%20Block%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20skeptical%20about%20AI%20claims%3B%20many%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20they%20had%20already%20been%20using%20AI%20at%20work%2C%20and%20didn't%20believe%20it%20could%20replace%20them%20outright.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolitano%20said%20that%2C%20in%20his%20view%2C%20AI%20is%20likely%20behind%20at%20least%20some%20of%20the%20tech%20labor%20market's%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20much%20of%20it%20you%20want%20to%20ascribe%20is%20really%20hard%20to%20tell%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20think%20it's%20a%20coincidence%20that%20computer%20system%20design%20is%20one%20of%20the%20industries%20that's%20losing%20the%20most%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20Politano%20said.%20And%2C%20while%20AI%20firms%20are%20hiring%2C%20they're%20bringing%20on%20far%20fewer%20employees%20than%20Big%20Tech%20behemoths.%20The%20types%20of%20jobs%20lost%2C%20and%20the%20timing%20of%20those%20losses%2C%20point%2C%20for%20Politano%2C%20to%20at%20least%20some%20impact%20from%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20clearly%20haven't%20seen%20the%20end%20of%20this%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Politano%20said%20of%20the%20future%20of%20the%20tech%20sector.%20%26quot%3BI%20expect%20that%20it%20will%20be%20this%20dribble%20of%20bad%20news%20for%20the%20near%20term%20going%20forward%2C%20but%20I%20just%20think%20that%20there's%20no%20positive%20evidence%20that%20we're%20breaking%20out%20of%20this%20post-2022%20cycle%20that%20tech%20has%20been%20stuck%20in.%20Until%20you%20see%20that%20kind%20of%20evidence%2C%20I%20think%20there's%20very%20little%20chance%20of%20a%20reversal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-jobs-getting-demolished-great-recession-dot-com-era-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772820996000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ab1479d3e2f1aef36a23f3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-jobs-getting-demolished-great-recession-dot-com-era-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It's%20a%20rough%20time%20to%20be%20looking%20for%20a%20tech%20job.%20Economist%20Joseph%20Politano%20said%20losses%20in%20the%20industry%20outpaced%20those%20in%20the%20last%20two%20recessions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jkaplan%40businessinsider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan%2CMadison%20Hoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-jobs-getting-demolished-great-recession-dot-com-era-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Spent%20night%20fearing%20explosions%E2%80%99%3A%20Passengers%20recount%20Iran%20war%20scare%20as%20first%20flight%20from%20Dubai%20lands%20in%20San%20Francisco%22%2C%22content%2