3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20woman%20in%20her%20early%2040s%20thought%20the%20blood%20she%20saw%20in%20the%20toilet%20was%20hemorrhoids.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMore%20than%20a%20year%20later%2C%20she%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20stage%203b%20colorectal%20cancer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExperts%20say%20rectal%20cancer%20is%20on%20the%20rise%20in%20people%20under%2050%2C%20and%20destigmatizing%20toilet%20talk%20is%20key.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELaura%20Behnke%20did%20not%20have%20time%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrue-cost-young-colon-cancer-crisis-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworry%20about%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20she%20first%20saw%20blood%20in%20the%20toilet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20trying%20in%20vitro%20fertilization%20for%20the%20fourth%20and%20final%20time%2C%20and%20her%20focus%20was%20on%20getting%20pregnant%20after%20three%20failed%20rounds%20with%20no%20healthy%20embryos.%20Everything%20else%20could%20wait.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20days%20before%20the%20implantation%20was%20scheduled%2C%20she%20saw%20a%20kind%20of%20red%20mucus%20coating%20her%20stool%2C%20and%20thought%3A%20%26quot%3B'I%20have%20been%20under%20an%20immense%20amount%20of%20stress.%20I%20know%20I've%20been%20straining.%20This%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-thought-she-had-hemorrhoids-was-diagnosed-colon-cancer-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20to%20be%20hemorrhoids%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20right%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20told%20myself%2C%20'You%20know%20what%3F%20Calm%20down%2C%20take%20some%20deep%20breaths%2C%20stop%20straining%2C%20and%20this%20will%20all%20go%20away%2C%20and%20it'll%20be%20fine%2C%20and%20you%20can%20go%20on%20and%20have%20a%20baby%2C'%26quot%3B%20Behnke%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20be%20over%20a%20year%20before%20she%20discovered%20she%20had%20rectal%20cancer%2C%20joining%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiagnosed-with-colon-cancer-only-had-one-symptom-stomach-pain-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrowing%20cohort%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20younger%20adults%20being%20diagnosed%20with%20the%20disease%20decades%20earlier%20than%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eexpected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aa34fe20-27e8-4f0e-8a9e-b64335b0c815%5C%22%3ECancer%20was%20not%20on%20her%20radar%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22laura%20with%20husband%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a9f7e8fd4fbd083f299e2d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BI%20felt%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20no%20way%20I%20could%20have%20cancer.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3Ecourtesy%20of%20Laura%20Behnke%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20that%20fourth%20round%20of%20IVF%2C%20at%20age%2041%2C%20Behnke%20did%20get%20pregnant.%20At%20first%2C%20she%20was%20shocked.%20Hearing%20a%20heartbeat%20at%20five%20weeks%20made%20it%20finally%20feel%20real.%20She%20was%20overjoyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBehnke%20continued%20to%20see%20some%20blood%20in%20the%20toilet%20intermittently%2C%20but%20it%20was%20easy%20to%20brush%20off%20because%20hemorrhoids%20are%20common%20during%20pregnancy.%20She%20didn't%20know%20the%20difference%20between%20the%20drops%20of%20blood%20typical%20for%20hemorrhoids%2C%20and%20the%20red%20mucus%20she%20saw%20that%20she%20now%20knows%20was%20characteristic%20of%20colorectal%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNobody%20at%20any%20point%20asked%20me%3A%20'What's%20the%20bleeding%20like%3F%20How%20often%20is%20it%20happening%3F'%26quot%3B%20Behnke%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20all%20just%20said%2C%20'Oh%2C%20hemorrhoids%2C%20cool.%20Moving%20on.%20We%20have%20other%20things%20to%20worry%20about.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20third%20trimester%2C%20Behnke%20did%20develop%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-symptoms-young-people-misdiagnosed-hemorrhoids-women-worldclass-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eswollen%20external%20hemorrhoid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20made%20it%20hurt%20to%20sit%20down.%20For%20two%20days%2C%20she%20tried%20not%20to%20put%20any%20pressure%20on%20her%20bottom.%20In%20the%20car%2C%20she%20sat%20on%20a%20donut%20pillow.%20On%20the%20couch%2C%20she%20laid%20on%20her%20side.%20This%20bleeding%20looked%20and%20felt%20different%2C%20like%20bright%20red%20food%20dye%20coloring%20the%20toilet%20bowl.%20She%20took%20medication%20to%20manage%20the%20pain%2C%20and%20got%20on%20with%20the%20business%20of%20getting%20ready%20to%20be%20a%20new%20mom.%20A%20few%20months%20later%2C%20her%20daughter%20was%20born.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22laura%20with%20baby%20and%20husband%2C%20before%20diagnosis%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a9f7e8d3e2f1aef36a1569%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBehnke%20was%20enjoying%20being%20a%20new%20mom%2C%20and%20felt%20fine.%20She%20assumed%20the%20blood%20she%20saw%20in%20the%20toilet%20was%20caused%20by%20hemorrhoids%2C%20swollen%20veins%20that%20can%20develop%20around%20the%20anus%2C%20which%20are%20a%20common%20side%20effect%20of%20pregnancy.%3Cp%3Ecourtesy%20of%20Laura%20Behnke%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20six%20months%20of%20sleepless%20nights%20and%20newborn%20feedings%2C%20Behnke%20was%20finally%20starting%20to%20feel%20like%20herself%20again.%20She%20was%20regaining%20her%20strength%2C%20losing%20weight%2C%20and%20feeling%20in%20control%20of%20her%20body%20after%20years%20of%20IVF%20treatments%20and%20a%20pregnancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20now%20though%2C%20Behnke%20saw%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frectal-bleeding-most-common-early-sign-of-colon-cancer-taboo-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebloody%20mucus%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20the%20toilet%20even%20when%20she%20didn't%20have%20a%20bowel%20movement%2C%20which%20she%20attributed%20to%20that%20pesky%20external%20hemorrhoid.%20Her%20bowels%20were%20also%20changing%20shape%2C%20and%20her%20stools%20sometimes%20coming%20out%20pencil%20thin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBehnke%20decided%20to%20see%20a%20colorectal%20surgeon%20to%20get%20the%20swollen%20hemorrhoid%20removed.%20The%20doctor%20asked%20her%20about%20all%20of%20her%20symptoms%2C%20sparing%20no%20details%20about%20the%20blood%20or%20the%20poop%2C%20and%20then%2C%20to%20her%20surprise%2C%20told%20Behnke%20she%20urgently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-detection-rates-increase-in-young-people-colonoscopies-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eneeded%20a%20colonoscopy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20could%20be%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20things%20other%20than%20cancer%2C%20but%20we%20need%20a%20colonoscopy%20to%20find%20out%20for%20sure%2C%26quot%3B%20Behnke%20remembers%20her%20doctor%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20over%20a%20year%20of%20bloody%20stools%2C%20that%20was%20the%20first%20time%20Behnke%20heard%20the%20word%20%26quot%3Bcancer%26quot%3B%20uttered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2249da9138-129c-40a3-b1e3-6b2b88479daf%5C%22%3ERectal%20cancer%20is%20on%20the%20rise%20among%20people%20in%20their%2040s%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22laura%20during%20treatment%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a9f7e81fb3fcb426490361%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBehnke%20went%20through%20radiation%2C%20chemotherapy%2C%20and%20then%20surgery%20to%20remove%20part%20of%20her%20colon.%3Cp%3Ecourtesy%20of%20Laura%20Behnke%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20doctor%20told%20Behnke%20she%20had%20late-stage%203b%20colorectal%20cancer%2C%20she%20broke%20down%20crying.%20%26quot%3BBut%20we%20have%20a%20seven-month-old!%26quot%3B%20she%20wailed%20into%20her%20husband's%20shoulder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20could%20I%20be%20that%20sick%20and%20feel%20that%20good%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20wondered.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20just%20had%20a%20completely%20normal%20and%20healthy%20pregnancy.%26quot%3B%20Suddenly%2C%20she%20felt%20a%20debt%20of%20gratitude%20to%20that%20annoying%20little%20hemorrhoid%20that%20led%20to%20her%20diagnosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20colonoscopy%20revealed%20that%20cancer%20had%20spread%20to%20some%20of%20the%20lymph%20nodes%20around%20her%20rectum%2C%20and%20was%20edging%20closer%20to%20other%20parts%20of%20her%20body.%20She%20was%20thankful%20that%20the%20prognosis%20was%20still%20relatively%20good.%20Doctors%20were%20confident%20they%20could%20wipe%20the%20organ%20clean%20with%20radiation%2C%20chemotherapy%2C%20and%20then%20surgery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2042-years-old%2C%20Behnke%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20what%20has%20quickly%20become%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-leading-cause-cancer-death-under-50-shocking-experts-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeadliest%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20people%20under%2050%20in%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20landscape%20of%20colorectal%20cancer%20is%20changing%20rapidly%2C%26quot%3B%20Rebecca%20Siegel%2C%20an%20epidemiologist%20and%20the%20senior%20scientific%20director%20of%20surveillance%20research%20at%20the%20American%20Cancer%20Society%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20don't%20know%20why%2C%20but%20many%20of%20these%20new%2C%20young-onset%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-rectal-cancer-rise-young-people-protect-yourself-lower-risk-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecolon%20cancer%20cases%20are%20rectal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20prompting%20bloody%20stools.%20Other%20common%20symptoms%20in%20this%20age%20group%20include%20persistent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-football-player-stabbing-stomach-pain-stage-4-colon-cancer-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estomach%20cramping%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20severe%20abdominal%20pain%2C%20low%20iron%20levels%2C%20and%20changes%20to%20bowel%20movements%2C%20including%20the%20narrower%20stools%20Behnke%20saw.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20suggests%20that%20bloody%20stools%20are%20an%20early%20warning%20sign%20for%20about%2040%25%20of%20rectal%20cancer%20patients.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20an%20opportunity%20for%20earlier%20diagnosis%2C%20but%20the%20problem%20is%2C%20especially%20for%20younger%20people%2C%20they're%20not%20aware%20of%20the%20symptoms%20and%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20talk%20about%20the%20symptoms%2C%26quot%3B%20Siegel%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20sometimes%20they%20even%20do%20go%20to%20the%20doctor%20with%20these%20symptoms%2C%20and%20they're%20diagnosed%20with%20hemorrhoids%20or%20something%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20couple%20of%20weeks%20after%20Behnke%20had%20her%20first%20dose%20of%20radiation%2C%20she%20stopped%20bleeding%20into%20the%20toilet.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAfter%2025%20sessions%20of%20radiation%2C%20then%20four%20months%20of%20chemotherapy%2C%20and%20finally%2C%20surgery%20that%20removed%20parts%20of%20her%20colon%20and%20rectum%2C%20she%20landed%20in%20diapers%20alongside%20her%20daughter%20for%20a%20few%20weeks.%20Doctors%20said%20every%20visible%20trace%20of%20the%20cancer%20was%20gone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESlowly%2C%20over%20time%2C%20her%20colon%20has%20healed%20and%20she's%20readjusted%20to%20a%20more%20normal%20bathroom%20routine%2C%20but%20she%20says%20things%20will%20never%20be%20quite%20the%20same%20down%20there.%20She%20prioritizes%20getting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-fiber-breakfast-prevent-colon-cancer-dietitian-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eplenty%20of%20fiber%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20her%20diet%20from%20colorful%20vegetables%2C%20and%20also%20takes%20fiber%20pills%20